		<div class="comment snook" id="c66942">
		<div class="meta">
			<div class="commentnumber"><a href="#c66942">34</a></div>
			<span class="authorname">Jonathan Snook</span> said on March 29, 2011		</div>
		<div class="quote"><p>@Justin: You're depending on the speed and availability of twitter on every page request. If Twitter goes down, a stalled request to their API could slow your site to a crawl. In my case, I pull in Twitter, Delicious, and Flickr feeds. These requests are cached so as not to impact every page view. You may not notice the performance issues on a small site but ramp up your traffic and you'll start to see bottlenecks.
</p>
</div>
	</div>
