		<div class="meta">
			<div class="commentnumber"><a href="#c66989">36</a></div>
			<span class="authorname">Jonathan Snook</span> said on March 31, 2011		</div>
		<div class="quote"><p>@Justin: If you're relying on a 3rd party API of any service on every request, then you still have to deal with the problem of it going down. If the servers are slow, when do you time things out? Your page should be loading in one or two seconds at most. The data used to build the page should be cached and/or locally accessible as much as possible.
</p>
